    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03223.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener rend="center">
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>652 NORTH EIGHTH STREET</name>
                <name type="place">Philadelphia.</name>
                <date when="1891-12-03"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Dec. 3. 1891.</date></dateline>
                <salute>Walt Whitman,</salute>
                <salute>My dear Sir;</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Pardon my recent neglect of your case. The reason of it is&#8212;I am badly used up after
                going through the brunt of a severe sore throat and bronchitis. I hope, before many days,
                to see you again and that, in the meantime, you will steer along cheerfully, hopefully, without
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03223.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.03223.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
                my captaincy, if I for the moment may assume such role.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>With kind regards</salute>
                <salute>I am</salute>
                <salute>Yours Sincerely.</salute>
                <signed>Daniel Longaker.</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.03223.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
